
[1]reformer

   REFORM'ER, n.

   1. One who effects a reformation or amendment; as a reformer of manners
   or of abuses.

   2. One of those who commenced the reformation of religion from popish
   corruption; as Luther, Melancthon, Zuinglius and Calvin.
